M. Todgers's Commercial Boarding House was a house of that sort which is likely to be dark at any time but that morning it was especially dark . 
In particular , there was a sensation of cabbage as if all the greens that had ever been boiled there , were evergreens , and flourished in immortal strength . 
The parlour was wainscoted , and communicated to strangers a magnetic and instinctive consciousness of rats and mice . 
