She wore a very rusty black gown , rather the worse for snuff , and a shawl and bonnet to correspond . 
The face of Mrs Gamp the nose in particular was somewhat red and swollen , and it was difficult to enjoy her society without becoming conscious of a smell of spirits . 
'Ah ! repeated Mrs Gamp for it was always a safe sentiment in cases of mourning . 
