Mr Mould and his men had not exaggerated the grandeur of the arrangements . 
The four hearse horses , especially , reared and pranced , and showed their highest action , as if they knew a man was dead , and triumphed in it . 
And as Mr Mould himself had said already , his behaviour was indecent , and quite unworthy of such an occasion and he never ought to have been there . 
But Chuffey , Heaven help him ! heard no sound but the echoes , lingering in his own heart , of a voice for ever silent . 
