Mr Pecksniff's house is more than a thousand leagues away and again this happy chronicle has Liberty and Moral Sensibility for its high companions . 
A poor fancy for steel and iron are of infinitely greater account , in this commonwealth , than flesh and blood . 
There were three great caravans or cars attached . 
The ladies' car , the gentlemen's car , and the car for negroes the latter painted black , as an appropriate compliment to its company . 
They were seated side by side , and were engaged in earnest conversation . 
'Were you not jolly there ? asked Martin . 
'On the contrairy , sir , returned Mark . 
'The jolliest week as ever I spent in my life , was that there week at Pawkins's . 
