Darn all manner of vermin . 
Martin could not help frowning for a moment , as if he were disposed to insinuate that the gentleman had unconsciously 'darned' himself . 
But remembering the wisdom of doing at Rome as Romans do , he smiled with the pleasantest expression he could assume upon so short a notice . 
Their new friend said no more just then , being busily employed in cutting a quid or plug from his cake of tobacco , and whistling softly to himself the while . 
'What do you call this now ? he asked . 
