, Bunker Hill Street , 'Monday Morning . 
'Sir I was raised in those interminable solitudes where our mighty Mississippi rolls his turbid flood . 
'I am young , and ardent . 
For there is a poetry in wildness , and every alligator basking in the slime is in himself an Epic , self contained . 
