He had scarcely got through this correspondence when Captain Kedgick , the landlord , kindly came upstairs to see how he was getting on . 
The Captain sat down upon the bed before he spoke and finding it rather hard , moved to the pillow . 
'Well , sir ! said the Captain , putting his hat a little more on one side , for it was rather tight in the crown 'You're quite a public man I calc'late . 
'So it seems , retorted Martin , who was very tired . 
'Our citizens , sir , pursued the Captain , 'intend to pay their respects to you . 
