But Mark was bent on solving the riddle of this lionship , if he could and so , not without the risk of being left behind , ran back to the hotel . 
Captain Kedgick was sitting in the colonnade , with a julep on his knee , and a cigar in his mouth . 
He caught Mark's eye , and said 'Why , what the 'Tarnal brings you here ? 'I'll tell you plainly what it is , Captain , said Mark . 
