I would have said , cried Mr Pecksniff , 'that the Serpent lied . 
Such was my faith in Thomas Pinch , that I would have cast the falsehood back into the Serpent's teeth , and would have taken Thomas to my heart . 
But I am not a Serpent , sir , myself , I grieve to say , and no excuse or hope is left me . 
Martin was greatly disturbed to see him so much agitated , and to hear such unexpected news . 
He begged him to compose himself , and asked upon what subject Mr Pinch's treachery had been developed . 
