Mr Moddle taking up the gauntlet , they played several rubbers for sixpences , and Charity won them all . 
On the seventh night of cribbage , when Mrs Todgers , sitting by , proposed that instead of gambling they should play for 'love , Mr Moddle was seen to change colour . 
On the fourteenth night , he kissed Miss Pecksniff's snuffers , in the passage , when she went upstairs to bed meaning to have kissed her hand , but missing it . 
with rising prospects , and 'almost' enough to live on . 
