'He'll come in , sir . 
Which turned out to be quite true , for he did . 
His face was almost as hard and knobby as his stick and so were his hands . 
His head was like an old black hearth broom . 
He sat down on the chest with his hat on and crossing his legs and looking up at Mark , said , without removing his pipe 'Well , Mr Co . 
! and how do you git along , sir ? It may be necessary to observe that Mr Tapley had gravely introduced himself to all strangers , by that name . 
