'What's come of all that chattering and swaggering ? He's wandering in his mind to night , and don't know me ! Martin indeed was dangerously ill very near his death . 
He lay in that state many days , during which time Mark's poor friends , regardless of themselves , attended him . 
He remembered nothing but the better qualities of his fellow wanderer , and was devoted to him , heart and hand . 
He was yet in a feeble and weak condition , when the misfourtune he had so much dreaded fell upon them . 
Mark fought against it but the malady fought harder , and his efforts were in vain . 
, they were twenty times kinder to Mark . 
At first sight there was nothing very distressing in these meditations , but they did undoubtedly distress him for all that . 
Selfishness does this especially so do suspicion , cunning , stealth , and covetous propensities . 
Martin had unconsciously reasoned as a child , 'My guardian takes so much thought of himself , that unless I do the like by MYself , I shall be forgotten . 
So he had grown selfish . 
But he had never known it . 
If any one had taxed him with the vice , he would have indignantly repelled the accusation , and conceived himself unworthily aspersed . 
It was natural for him to reflect he had months to do it in upon his own escape , and Mark's extremity . 
, whether he had done his duty by him , and had deserved and made a good response to his fidelity and zeal . 
So low had Eden brought him down . 
So high had Eden raised him up . 
, Mark showed some symptoms of returning health . 
They came and went , and flickered for a time but he began to mend at last decidedly and after that continued to improve from day to day . 
'Ours is a desperate case , said Martin . 
The place is deserted its failure must have become known and selling what we have bought to any one , for anything , is hopeless , even if it were honest . 
We left home on a mad enterprise , and have failed . 
The only hope left us , the only one end for which we have now to try , is to quit this settlement for ever , and get back to England . 
Anyhow ! by any means ! only to get back there , Mark . 
