'My grandfather did ? said Martin . 
'Yes spoke to me alone , and told me 'What the hound had said , cried Martin . 
'And said I knew well what qualities he possessed that he was moderately rich in good repute and high in his favour and confidence . 
But seeing me very much distressed , he said that he would not control or force my inclinations , but would content himself with telling me the fact . 
He would not pain me by dwelling on it , or reverting to it nor has he ever done so since , but has truly kept his word . 
'The man himself ? asked Martin . 
