Dear Martin , I must tell you , she continued , 'that the kindness of your grandfather to me remains unchanged . 
I am his companion still . 
An indescribable tenderness and compassion seem to have mingled themselves with his old regard and if I were his only child , I could not have a gentler father . 
Martin looked with admiration on her glowing face , and pressed his lips to hers . 
But the influence this fellow exercises over him has steadily increased , I fear . 
She could not help admitting that . 
Steadily , imperceptibly , and surely , until it was paramount and supreme . 
She herself had none and yet he treated her with more affection than at any previous time . 
Martin thought the inconsistency a part of his weakness and decay . 
'Does the influence extend to fear ? said Martin . 
'Is he timid of asserting his own opinion in the presence of this infatuation ? I fancied so just now . 
'I have thought so , often . 
He has broken off immediately , and become what you have seen to day . 
When we first came here he had his impetuous outbreaks , in which it was not easy for Mr Pecksniff with his utmost plausibility to appease him . 
But these have long since dwindled away . 
He defers to him in everything , and has no opinion upon any question , but that which is forced upon him by this treacherous man . 
