Let him be discomfited in one quarter , and he refreshed and recompensed himself by carrying the war into another . 
He had never been such a saintly and improving spectacle to all about him , as after his detection by Thomas Pinch . 
He had scarcely ever been at once so tender in his humanity , and so dignified and exalted in his virtue , as when young Martin's scorn was fresh and hot upon him . 
