'The set of jewels and the wearer are so well matched , said the old man , 'that I don't know which becomes the other most . 
Mr Westlock could tell me , I have no doubt , but I'll not ask him , for he is bribed . 
There are not many fathers who marry two such daughters on the same day but we will overlook the improbability for the gratification of an old man's fancy . 
